The correct implementation for Floyd's Tortoise and Hare algorithm to detect a cycle in a linked list is as follows:

public static boolean hasCycle(ListNode head) {
    ListNode slow = head;
    ListNode fast = head;
    while (fast != null && fast.next != null) {
        slow = slow.next;
        fast = fast.next.next; // The fast pointer must move two steps at a time.
        if (slow == fast) {
            return true;
        }
    }
    return false;
}
